--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
version 1.16.0.0  |  2014-07-14  |
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
CHG Removed support of legacy API of the Linux procfs. Support only seqfile for
    all procfs output. [VOICECPE_SW-744]
FIX Adaptions due to the change of the internal fifo implementation.
    [VOICECPE_SW-574]
FIX Fixed lockup of GR909 test after a capacitance measurement was done.
    [VOICECPE_SW-731]
FIX Fixed possible memory leak in BBD download. [VOICECPE_SW-734]
CHG Adapted to changed MPS driver API with only event mailbox support.
    [VOICECPE_SW-720]
NEW Support compilation as Linux platform driver with configuration via device
    tree. Unified driver to support all XRX200 and XRX300 devices with just a
    single binary. [VOICECPE_SW-723][VOICECPE_SW-673]
CHG Adapted to changes in MPS driver to remove the support for FW without
    event mailbox. [VOICECPE_SW-720]
FIX Corrected denying of system clock frequency reduction which did sometimes
    not work in the new CPU frequency implementation. [VOICECPE_SW-715]
NEW Added configure option --enable-pmc-if=X to select the type of interface
    to use towards the PMC module. Using this also make will detect what needs
    to be recompiled. [VOICECPE_SW-551]
CHG Required firmware version on XRX300: 1.4.0, XRX200: 3.4.0
NEW The elapsed time since the last hook which is reported in every hook event
    is now taken from the firmware event message if the FW supports this.
    [VOICECPE_SW-534] [VOICECPE_SW-712]
FIX Separated the preprocessor defines for the clock frequency change feature.
    [VOICECPE_SW-704]
FIX Added compile switches around RTCP-XR implementation. [VOICECPE_SW-599]
FIX Corrected mutual protection of code reported by klocwork. [VOICECPE_SW-706]
CHG Adaptions to changed API of the clock frequency change mechanism in UGW6.1.
    Report when full clock frequency is no longer needed. Get function reports
    the last set system state. Moved the clock handling from the device into
    the driver context. The registration with the PMCU is now already done when
    the driver is started. Prevent clock frequency reduction while the FW is
    started. [VOICECPE_SW-704] [VOICECPE_SW-705]
CHG Deactivated the previous PMU interface for UGW6.1 as this is done
    differently there. [VOICECPE_SW-673]
CHG Adaptions to UGW 6.1 including support of Linux kernel up to 3.10.12.
    [VOICECPE_SW-673]
NEW Configuration of PCM to wideband with split time slots if supported by FW.
    [VOICECPE_SW-729]
NEW Added display of the PCM timeslot allocation map to the "statistics" node of
    the linux proc filesystem.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
version 1.15.1.x  |  2013-11-22  |  Voice System Package 4.33 branch
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
CHG Required firmware version on XRX300: 1.3.0, XRX200: 3.3.0
CHG Allowed direct change of linefeeding from disabled to active.
NEW Added autonomous recovery for short SSI bus faults due to ESD events on
    the hardware. [VOICECPE_SW-635] [VOICECPE_SW-650]
CHG Renamed the Linux /proc filesystem node "statistics" into "status".
CHG Adapted to changed include filenames of drivers in UGW6.1. [VOICECPE_SW-666]
CHG Remove obsolete use of the Linux big kernel lock from TAPI_OS_ThreadKill()
    function. [VOICECPE_SW-668]
CHG Adapt to changes of IFXOS from 1.5.17 to 1.5.19. [VOICECPE_SW-667]
FIX Corrected several compiler warnings. [VOICECPE_SW-571]
NEW The first BBD download now automatically does an analog line calibration
    to find individual correction values. This prevents clipping and noise in
    all analog operations but specifically with the combined DC/DC converter.
    As a sideeffect the BBD download now takes about half a second per channel.
    [VOICECPE_SW-658]
FIX Removed reporting an timeout error when a linefeed change is not confirmed
    by the firmware because no change actually occured. [VOICECPE_SW-657]
FIX Removed solution in driver to prevent SSI crash when setting both lines
    to IFX_TAPI_LINE_FEED_PHONE_DETECT at the same time. The root cause was
    found and fixed in the voice-FW. [VOICECPE_SW-639]
FIX Further improved the waiting for linefeeding changes. [VOICECPE_SW-634]
    [VOICECPE_SW-400]
FIX Changed the waiting for linefeeding changes. Now blocking only occurs when
    the previous linefeed change has not yet completed. With this the cadenced
    ringing does not get delayed waiting for a change to happen. Also times for
    CID in association with ringing are back to normal. [VOICECPE_SW-634]
    [VOICECPE_SW-654] [VOICECPE_SW-400]
FIX Added check for allowed values of the redundancy parameter of the encoder
    setting message. Values not applicable for the selected encoder will be
    silently ignored while incorrect values will result in an error.
    [VOICECPE_SW-653]
NEW Added debugging support for printing details of an SSI crash.
    [VOICECPE_SW-650]
FIX Report error when AMR-NB or AMR-WB encoder are requested but not supported
    by the firmware. [VOICECPE_SW-649]
FIX Corrected reporting of AMR-WB codec for Decoder Change event.
    [VOICECPE_SW-626]
FIX Corrected reporting of SSI activity status on systems with SLIC120 so that
    during sleep clock lowering is possible. [VOICECPE_SW-646]
FIX For IFX_TAPI_CAP_CHECK added missing capabilities IFX_TAPI_CAP_TYPE_FXO and
    IFX_TAPI_CAP_TYPE_DCDC. [VOICECPE_SW-645]
FIX Corrected recording of the CPTD activation for the power state reporting
    when more than one CPTD is used on one channel. [VOICECPE_SW-644]
NEW Added IFX_TAPI_CAP_TYPE_DCDC to the capability list so that the application
    can choose the BBD file matching the connected DC/DC type. Require also the
    BBD download for all connected DC/DC converters which are not the default
    inverting buck-boost type. Added reporting of the connected DC/DC converter
    and the configured DC/DC configuration to the Linux /proc filesystem.
    [VOICECPE_SW-636]
CHG Adapted to the changed API of the PMCU that resolves a lockup of the driver
    when clock changes are disabled by administration. [VOICECPE_SW-641]
FIX Removed additional code made obsolete by the OPC event. Regardless of the
    reported linefeed allow setting the line to disabled. [VOICECPE_SW-400]
CHG When reloading the FW with FIO_MPS_DOWNLOAD without a IFX_TAPI_DEV_STOP
    first an implicit stop is done. [VOICECPE_SW-640]
FIX Prevent SSI crash when setting both lines to IFX_TAPI_LINE_FEED_PHONE_DETECT
    at the same time. [VOICECPE_SW-639]
FIX Fixed crash occuring several seconds after DevStop while any of the phones
    was off-hook at that time. [VOICECPE_SW-652]

