version 1.15.0.x  |  2013-06-04  |  Voice System Package 4.32 branch
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
NEW Support combined DC/DC converter for SmartSLIC. [VOICECPE_SW-636]
NEW Support for voice system clock frequencies below 200MHz when all FXS ports
    are either standby or disabled and a possible FXO port is on-hook.
    [VOICECPE_SW-470] [VOICECPE_SYS-267]
CHG Support for AMR was changed as follows:
    - AMR is selected with IFX_TAPI_ENC_TYPE_AMR_NB or IFX_TAPI_ENC_TYPE_AMR_WB
      and addtionally the encoder bitrate. Please check in the system package
      release note which codecs are actually supported.
    - Removed IOCTL for AMR specific settings VMMC_TAPI_LL_COD_AMR_Set.
      AMR redundancy is now set with IOCTL VMMC_TAPI_LL_COD_ENC_Cfg_Set.
    [VOICECPE_SW-626]
CHG Added check of supported codec to the announcement feature.
NEW Partial support od RTCP-XR. [VOICECPE_SW-599]
CHG On the DECT channel the UTG generated tone is now mixed with the voice
    signal instead of blocking it. [VOICECPE_SW-606]
CHG SDD firmware commands are moved to a separate header file. [VOICECPE_SW-334]
CHG Added waiting for OPC event after opmode change. [VOICECPE_SW-400]
CHG Removed Danube (SLIC-DC) support. [VOICECPE_SW-572]
FIX Issue with GR909 measurements not being executed when both channels
    in standby mode. [VOICECPE_SW-590]

