version 1.12.0.2  |  2012-08-21  |  Voice System Package 4.28 RC1 / UGW 5.3 W6
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
CHG Added support for Linux cpufreq kernel driver in addition to the existing
    PMCU support. [VOICECPE_SW-453]
FIX Set unused values in the analog line calibration results to 0 instead of
    IFX_TAPI_CALIBRATION_UNUSED.
CHG Removed Line Testing library files. [VOICECPE_SW-497]
NEW Added two new version fields to the struct VMMC_IO_VERSION that is the
    parameter of FIO_GET_VERS. Field nEDSPTimestamp contains the time and date
    the FW was build and field nEDSPVariant contains the last digit of the FW
    version. The complete firmware version number is the sequence from these
    fields: "nEdspVers.nEdspIntern.nEDSPHotFix.nType.nEDSPVariant".
    [VOICECPE_SW-301]
FIX Corrected capacitance measurement - IFX_TAPI_Event_Dispatch() was protected
    by semaphor when capacitance measurement result was read. This caused
    system hung up.
NEW Added support for Line Testing library - capacitance measurement.
CHG Added support for extended linetesting as it is supported by the DUSLIC-xT
    device driver to lib_lt. [VOICECPE_SW-450]
FIX Avoid blocking of voice data downstream traffic while IOCTLs are executed.
    [VOICECPE_SW-476]
FIX Reset internal error flags on FW download to allow a start of the FW also
    in the case of previous errors. [VOICECPE_SW-424]
NEW Added printout of the SSI bus condition to the linux proc node "statistic".
    [VOICECPE_SW-422]
CHG New dependency table for PMCU.
CHG Updated recommended FW versions for Danube, AR9, VR9 and FALC ON-V.
CHG Cleaned double doxygen documentation and unused symbol definitions from
    voice-FW interface file.
CHG Removed legacy code that supported the no longer used event signalling via
    bitfields of the voice-FW. Refactored registration of the event callback
    handlers. [VOICECPE_SW-399]
FIX Added reporting of SLIC temperature to the continuous measurement dataset.
    [VOICECPE_SW-404]
FIX Previously not set direction fields of the CPTD event are now set according
    to the direction from which the tone was detected. [VOICECPE_SW-402]
FIX Changed sequence in device stop to disable interrupts right after stopping
    the algorithms on the channels. Explicitly mask all interrupts on MPS level
    when the first callback is deregistered. [VOICECPE_SW-342]

